### Automatically Generate a Table of Contents in LaTeX

To generate a table of contents (ToC) automatically in a LaTeX document, you can use the following commands:

1. **\tableofcontents**: This command generates the ToC at the beginning of the document.

2. **\addcontentsline**: This command adds an entry to the ToC.

3. **\chapter**, **\section**, **\subsection**, etc.: These commands create the headings in the document.

Here's an example of how to use these commands:

```  
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}
\tableofcontents % Generate the ToC

\section{Introduction}
This is the introduction.

\section{Methods}
This is the methods section.

\section{Results}
This is the results section.

\section{Discussion}
This is the discussion section.

\end{document}
```

In this example, the `\tableofcontents` command generates the ToC at the beginning of the document. The `\section` commands create the headings in the document, and the `\addcontentsline` command adds an entry to the ToC for each section.

